User Datagram Protocol
UDP is transport layer protocol
DATAGRAM as PDU term

-- Does NOT provide acknowledgement
-- Unreliable - We cannot know that a UDP packet arrived. 
* Used often for streaming

-- 64 bit (8 byte) header. 
-- Header is 16 bits for source port number

* SNMP uses UDP for management processes
* DNS, VOIP, Multicasting
* Some 


